author: julianfoad
msg: In the WC storage of tree conflict info, add a missing entry in a conversion
table for completeness. Even though the missing entry has no current or
expected use, the API implies that any enumeration value is allowed at this
level, so the table should be complete.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/tree_conflicts.c
(reason_map): Add an entry for "unversioned", which was missing from the
map.

author: julianfoad
msg: Tweak the new conflict description word for "replace", added in r38903,
for consistency with the other words. This affects the format of metadata
stored in the entries file, but this "replace" keyword has not yet been in
a released version so there is no compatibility impact.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/tree_conflicts.c
(action_map): Change "replace" to "replaced" for consistency with the
other tokens in the map.

author: xsteve
msg: Implement svn update+commit via tramp+ssh
* trunk/contrib/client-side/emacs/psvn.el:
(svn-post-process-svn-output-hook): Add svn-fixup-tramp-output-maybe
(svn-local-filename-for-remote-access): New function to convert a full
qualified filename (including a host) to a local name
(svn-fixup-tramp-output-maybe): New function to fixup a leftover exit
text line at the end of the svn output
(svn-status-update-cmd): Make work with tramp+ssh
(svn-log-edit-done): Make work with tramp+ssh
